NOTE (read before using): The original offer text has been annotated. Replace bracketed text and implement the signed annexes described. This redline presumes the Parties will execute the offer and separate IP Assignment & Data Processing Annex. The legal team must insert actual company names, mentor names, dates, and ensure signature lines are present.

---- START REDLINE ----

[Header and recipient details as in original document]

1. Position and Purpose
Original text: "You are offered the position of AI Intern..."
REVISED (replace with):
"Position and Purpose. The Parties agree that this engagement is a fixed-term Internship for training and professional development. The Intern will be assigned an Omninuera mentor, specific learning objectives, and project deliverables. This Internship is educational in nature and intended primarily for learning; it is not a contract of employment. The Internship will run for a fixed term of three (3) months commencing on [start date] and ending on [end date]."

Contractor note: Add explicit mentor name and reporting cadence.

2. Working Hours
Original: [existing hours language]
REVISED:
"Working hours. The Internship requires up to thirty (30) hours per week. Scheduling will be flexible to accommodate academic commitments. The Intern will not be required to work hours equivalent to full-time employees of Omninuera unless expressly agreed in writing."

3. Stipend, Taxes, and Statutory Compliance
Original: "You will be paid INR 10,000/month."
REVISED (replace with):
"Stipend. Omninuera will pay a stipend of INR 10,000 per month to assist with living expenses during the Internship. The stipend is intended as a training reimbursement. Taxation. The stipend is subject to applicable tax withholding. If the Intern is treated by Omninuera or a tax authority as an employee for tax purposes, Omninuera will deduct tax under Section 192 of the Income Tax Act, 1961 as required. If the stipend is treated as payments to a contractor/consultant by Omninuera, Omninuera may deduct such tax as required under applicable TDS provisions (e.g., Sections 194C/194J). The Intern shall provide PAN and any documentation or declarations (e.g., Form 15G/H) required by Omninuera for tax purposes."

Add statutory compliance backstop:
"Statutory compliance. If a competent authority determines that the Intern is an ‘employee’ for statutory purposes (including Minimum Wages Act, Employees’ Provident Fund, Employees’ State Insurance), Omninuera shall comply with applicable law and may make any adjustments to payments or register for contributions as required by law. Omninuera reserves the right to recover employee-share contributions to the extent permitted."

4. Termination and Final Settlement
REVISED:
"Termination. Either party may terminate this Internship by seven (7) calendar days’ prior written notice. Omninuera may terminate immediately for Gross Misconduct or material breach. On termination, Omninuera will pay the pro‑rata stipend earned up to the date of termination within fourteen (14) days, subject to lawful deductions permitted by applicable statutes. If the Intern is found to have committed gross misconduct, Omninuera may withhold amounts to the extent permitted by law."

5. Intellectual Property (NEW — MUST ADD)
Insert full clause as suggested in research:
"IP Assignment. The Intern hereby irrevocably assigns to Omninuera all right, title and interest in any Works, inventions, designs, discoveries or deliverables created by the Intern during the Internship which relate to Omninuera’s business. This assignment includes all copyright, moral rights (waiver to extent permitted by law), patent rights and other proprietary rights. The Intern agrees to execute any documents necessary to record or effect the assignment and to cooperate with Omninuera in patent filings. This IP assignment will be set out in a separate IP Assignment and Waiver Agreement to be executed concurrently with this offer."

6. Confidentiality (NEW / IMPROVED)
Insert:
"Confidentiality. The Intern shall maintain confidentiality of Omninuera Confidential Information during the Internship and for two (2) years following the conclusion of the Internship, except that trade secrets and proprietary technical information shall remain subject to confidentiality for as long as such information remains confidential. Exclusions: public domain, independently developed, or disclosed by legal compulsion. The Intern will return all materials on termination."

7. Background Checks and Data Protection (NEW)
Insert:
"The Intern consents to background verification and the processing of personal data necessary for onboarding. Omninuera will process personal data in accordance with applicable law, implement reasonable security measures, and retain data for no longer than necessary. For any cross-border transfers, Omninuera will obtain necessary consents and implement safeguards."

8. No Employment
Strengthen the clause:
"No employment. The Parties agree this Internship does not create an employment relationship. The Intern will not be eligible for employee benefits (including gratuity), except as expressly provided. Nothing in this Agreement prevents a future employment offer, which would require a separate written employment agreement."

9. Insurance and Welfare (NEW — recommended)
Insert:
"Insurance. Omninuera will provide personal accident insurance coverage for the Intern for the duration of the Internship. The Intern should notify Omninuera immediately of any illness or injury occurring in the course of the Internship."

10. Jurisdiction
Insert:
"Governing law and jurisdiction. This Agreement is governed by Indian law. The courts at Bengaluru, Karnataka shall have exclusive jurisdiction over disputes, subject to the Company’s right to seek interim relief elsewhere."

11. Signature block
Add signature lines for Intern and authorized signatory for Omninuera, with date and location. Include Annexes:
- Annex A: IP Assignment (signed).
- Annex B: Confidentiality & Data Processing Consent (signed).
- Annex C: Background Check Consent & Release.

